Absolutely amazing to see all of Frank's iconic work in real life, and she's constantly looking to get more of his work back whenever she can.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gWgo9rr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Frank Frazetta, painting at age 10. Crazy.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JLBdTQy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some Frazetta works to feast your eyes on...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Brq40qK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The inspiration for 'Slave Leia' in Return of the Jedi</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GgI6rQu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Jgqc1br.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1iY1n1a.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That's all.

Just wanted to share Sara's post, and do a quick Frazetta appreciation post.

Have an awesome day!

